3.10	Squatting_in_England	Squatting in England	Squatting in England usually refers to a person, not being the owner of a property, taking occupation of an empty house. People squat for a variety of reasons which include needing a home, protest, poverty and recreation. Criminal law refers to an "occupier" or "trespasser", and Civil Procedure Rules part 55 refer to possession claims against "trespassers".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9e/LondonSocialCentreRussellSquareSquat1_20060329KaihsuTai.jpg/220px-LondonSocialCentreRussellSquareSquat1_20060329KaihsuTai.jpg
